From c161b3b70e3d1f5725dc46cea08fe51e223cba16 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel Golle <daniel@makrotopia.org>
Date: Tue, 24 Feb 2026 23:31:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 17/24] lib: add portable UUID helper for lowercase output

Linux libuuid's uuid_unparse() emits lowercase hex, while OSSP uuid
(macOS / BSD) emits uppercase.  This produces different formatted
output across platforms, breaking tests and user expectations.

Add lib/utils_uuid.h with a static inline crypt_uuid_unparse() that
wraps uuid_unparse_lower() where available (detected via meson's
has_function check for HAVE_UUID_UNPARSE_LOWER), falling back to
uuid_unparse() plus tolower() on platforms without it.

Replace all uuid_unparse() calls across the codebase with
crypt_uuid_unparse() so that UUID strings are always lowercase,
matching the Linux kernel convention.
